calendar_id.description: Google Calendar ID. The format should follow {user_name}@{domain}.
calendar_id.title: Calendar Id

time_max.description: Upper bound (exclusive) for an event's start time to filter by. Optional. The default is current time + 30 days. Must be an RFC3339 timestamp with mandatory time zone offset, for example, 2011-06-03T10:00:00-07:00, 2011-06-03T10:00:00Z. Milliseconds may be provided but are ignored. If timeMin is set, timeMax must be greater than timeMin.
time_max.title: Time Max

time_min.description: Lower bound (exclusive) for an event's end time to filter by. Optional. The default is current time Must be an RFC3339 timestamp with mandatory time zone offset, for example, 2011-06-03T10:00:00-07:00, 2011-06-03T10:00:00Z. Milliseconds may be provided but are ignored. If timeMax is set, timeMin must be smaller than timeMax.
time_min.title: Time Min

event_types.description:
Event types to return. Optional. This parameter can be repeated multiple times to return events of different types. If unset, returns all event types.

Acceptable values are:
- 'birthday': Special all-day events with an annual recurrence.
- 'default': Regular events.
- 'focusTime': Focus time events.
- 'fromGmail': Events from Gmail.
- 'outOfOffice': Out of office events.
- 'workingLocation': Working location events.
event_types.title: Event Types

max_results.description: Maximum number of events returned on one result page.
max_results.title: Max Results
